dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public rights-of-way (ROWs) exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

February 2012 data updates compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2011; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal. However, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.
August 2015 through 2020 data updates compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over NMCOG 2014 Pictometry orthophotos; these orthos are known to be +/- 3.5' horizontal. procstep.procdesc: Existing parcel data was imported to MassGIS Level 3 template geodatabase.
Adjacent and non-contiguous parcels linked to the same Assessor’s record (based on the Assessor’s Map) were copied to the M081OthLeg featureclass and merged and marked as “TAX” in M081TaxPar.
Spatial accuracy of the data was verified using the parcel standard guidelines and 2011 orthophotography. Parcel topology was corrected using ArcGIS Desktop Advanced topology editing tools
The most recent extract of the Assessor’s data (3/14/12) was formatted and imported into the Level 3 template schema
Adjustments to parcel/ROW boundaries were made to address extreme differences between GIS area vs. Assessor’s lot size where possible.
LOC_ID was generated for each parcel and added to each record in the M081Assess table and M081OthLeg

srcinfo.srccontr: Existing parcel data produced by NMCOG and updated most recently in 2011; provided the basic spatial features used for Level 3 compliance development.

procstep.procdesc: MassGIS QA tools were run to identify and correct remaining errors

Parcel boundaries, ROW, and easements were updated and revised based on: the Assessor's MassGIS-format extract from May 28, 2014; Cuoco & Cormier CAD data and assessor maps from February 26, 2014; and Middlesex North Registry of Deeds plans recorded between October 1, 2011 and May 29, 2014.

To complete 8/5/2015 parcel updates, a Patriot Properties MassGIS-formatted extract was provided by the Dunstable Assessor's office and formatted to replace the M081Assess table. Survey bearings and distances were entered from Registry plans using COGO and tied to Town of Dunstable Survey Control monuments points where possible. Traverses or plans were georectified to visual reference points on 2014 Pictometry orthophotos (e.g. stone walls) where survey control was not available or inconsistent. MassGIS QA level 3 QA tool version 5.2 was run on the updated data.

To complete 10/13/2016 parcel updates, a Patriot Properties MassGIS-formatted extract was provided by the Dunstable Assessor's office and formatted to replace the M081Assess table. The MassGIS Assess load tool was used. Survey bearings and distances were entered from Registry plans using COGO and tied to Town of Dunstable Survey Control monuments points where possible. Traverses or plans were georectified to visual reference points on 2014 Pictometry orthophotos (e.g. stone walls) where survey control was not available or inconsistent. MassGIS QA level 3 QA tool version 5.2 was run on the updated data.

overview.dsoverv: This data represents property ownership (tax parcel polygons) for Dunstable, MA, based on the Assessor's tax maps revised March 2012. The data was developed to meet the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files version 2.1 (Level-3 compliance) based initially on existing parcel boundaries in shapefile format. Features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M081Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. The data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M081OthLeg and M081Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’s Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
